    },
    {
      "overview_item_type": "essential_ideas",
      "overview_item_content_type": "html",
      "overview_item_title": "Essential Ideas",
      "overview_item_data": {
        "overview_item_data_type": "list",
        "overview_item_data_items": [
          "An equation for a non-proportional linear relationship is <math><mi>y</mi><mo>=</mo><mi>m</mi><mi>x</mi><mo>+</mo><mi>b</mi></math>, where <math><mi>m</mi></math> is the slope and <math><mi>b</mi></math> is the y-coordinate of the point where the graph crosses the y-axis.",
          "The equation <math><mi>y</mi><mo>=</mo><mi>m</mi><mi>x</mi><mo>+</mo><mi>b</mi></math> represents every point <math><mo stretchy="false">(</mo><mi>x</mi><mo>,</mo><mi>y</mi><mo stretchy="false">)</mo></math> on the graph of the line.",
          "The slope of a line describes steepness and direction.",
          "The slope of a line that decreases from left to right is negative.",
          "You can use the properties of similar triangles constructed on a line to explain why the slope is the same for any two points on a line.",
          "The slope formula is <math><mi>m</mi><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mrow><msub><mi>y</mi><mn>2</mn></msub><mo>-</mo><msub><mi>y</mi><mn>1</mn></msub></mrow><mrow><msub><mi>x</mi><mn>2</mn></msub><mo>-</mo><msub><mi>x</mi><mn>1</mn></msub></mrow></mfrac></math>."
        ]
      }
    },
